# pins.env -- version pin for the sandbox provisioning wrappers.
#
# This file is the ONLY moving part of the sandbox/ tree (see
# docs/design/PROVISION.DESIGN.md, "Sandbox wrapper tree"). All behavioral
# churn lives inside clai, behind this pin: rolling out new provisioning
# behavior to every provider = editing this file in ONE reviewed change
# (the pin bump is the review gate, per the supply-chain stance documented
# in .claude/hooks/session-start.sh and ai-tools issue #72).
#
# Sourced (and exported) by sandbox/provision.sh, and read as a --pins file by
# `lmde acquire` (keys CLAI_VERSION + AST_MCP_VERSION). Plain KEY="value"
# assignments only -- no logic, no command substitution. `lmde acquire` NEVER
# edits this file; it only reads it.
#
# CLAI_VERSION is now the CONTENT-STAMP review gate (#145). Skills + the MCP
# catalog no longer float on a bare push to template-tools: they ride INSIDE
# the clai wheel's _data, so a skill or catalog edit reaches sandboxes only
# after a clai RELEASE and a CLAI_VERSION bump HERE. The pin bump is the
# review gate -- this is the accepted, WANTED consequence of #145 (a skill
# edit is a reviewed change, not a silent default-branch push).
#
# With NO --pins, `lmde acquire` floats BOTH packages to registry latest; the
# sandbox always passes --pins THIS file so the review gate applies. An UNSET
# key here means "float THAT package to latest" (loud-but-open, same as
# CLAI_VERSION below) -- a half-populated file pins one and floats the other by
# that rule, never by accident.
#
# Delivery transport (RD1, #101): clai is installed from GitHub Packages
# (npm.pkg.github.com) as @nine-at-a-time-media/clai, NOT fetched as a
# GitHub Release wheel over api.github.com -- that path is blocked by the
# Claude web agent proxy. The old CLAI_SHA256 wheel-digest pin is retired
# (RD3): npm verifies every downloaded tarball against the registry's
# published integrity hash, and a published version on GitHub Packages is
# immutable -- so the supply-chain gate is the pinned VERSION plus npm's
# built-in integrity check. The #72 stance is intact: a default-branch
# push still does not grant execution in a consumer, because consumers
# install the pinned released version.
#
# To bump the pin: set CLAI_VERSION to a released, published version of
# @nine-at-a-time-media/clai (`npm view @nine-at-a-time-media/clai version
# --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com` reports the latest -- the explicit
# registry is required, else npm queries registry.npmjs.org and fails for
# this private scoped package; a classic read:packages token must be
# configured for the scope). If it is ever reset to UNSET, provision.sh
# fails LOUDLY-but-open: it logs the fill-in procedure and exits 0 so
# sessions still start.

# clai (executable code: pinned version, npm registry integrity). Session
# hook scripts ship INSIDE this package (installed by `clai hooks
# install`), so they roll out via the same CLAI_VERSION bump -- no
# separate hooks pin.
# Current pin: @nine-at-a-time-media/clai@0.5.5 (published on GitHub
# Packages; an npm wrapper around clai's self-contained shiv .pyz).
#
# 0.5.5 (template-tools#144) is the first release whose MCP generator honors
# RD5: the canonical manifest names ${HOME}/.local/bin/ast-mcp, emitted
# LITERAL into the committed .mcp.json (Claude expands it in the spawned
# server's process) and RESOLVED to an absolute path in the user-scope
# codex/agy/opencode configs (those clients do not expand variables). Every
# earlier clai rewrote .mcp.json back to the unexpandable ${AST_MCP_BIN} on
# every provision run, so pinning below 0.5.5 reintroduces that regression.
CLAI_VERSION="0.5.5"

# ast-mcp (executable MCP server: pinned version, npm registry integrity).
# Installed by `lmde acquire` at ~/.local/bin/ast-mcp from GitHub Packages as
# @nine-at-a-time-media/ast-mcp. Same UNSET/loud-but-open convention as
# CLAI_VERSION: a real value pins that exact version; UNSET (or an absent key)
# floats ast-mcp to registry latest. Pinning both here through one --pins file
# is what gates the whole tooling surface in ONE reviewed change.
# To bump: `npm view @nine-at-a-time-media/ast-mcp version
# --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com` (with a classic read:packages token
# configured) reports the latest published version; set it and land via PR.
AST_MCP_VERSION="latest"

# Canonical source repos (stable; not pins). Skills and the MCP manifest
# are inert data and float to the latest default branch of
# TEMPLATE_TOOLS_REPO -- they are deliberately NOT pinned here. Post-#84
# the whole fleet publishes from template-tools, so both names point at
# the same repo (single owner -> one token covers the bootstrap).
# TEMPLATE_TOOLS_REPO is exported for `clai provision`; AI_TOOLS_REPO is
# retained for compatibility and slated for cleanup once no wrapper
# references it.
TEMPLATE_TOOLS_REPO="nine-at-a-time-media/template-tools"
AI_TOOLS_REPO="nine-at-a-time-media/template-tools"
